# Project rules

TanStack Start (Vite) + React 19 + Tailwind v4 + shadcn (Base UI) + Paraglide i18n.
Bun is the package manager; Node executes the tooling and serves production.

## Commands

- `bun run test` / `bun run build` — **never** `bun test` / `bun build`, which invoke
  Bun's own runner and bundler instead of the project scripts.
- `bun run lint` (oxlint, type-aware) · `bun run format:write` (oxfmt) ·
  `bun run type-check` · `bun run test:e2e` (Playwright, production bundle).
- Bun is pinned to **canary**: `bun.lock` is lockfileVersion 2 and bun 1.3.x cannot
  parse it. The Dockerfile and `.github/setup/action.yml` pin it too — change all three together.

## Never edit generated or vendored files

- `src/routeTree.gen.ts` — regenerated by the TanStack Start plugin.
- `src/i18n/**` — regenerated by Paraglide from `messages/*.json`.
- `src/components/ui/**` — vendored shadcn registry code; `shadcn add` overwrites it.
  Wrap it instead of forking it.

After adding a route, run `bun run dev` once so the route tree regenerates, or `tsc`
will not know the route exists.

## Tooling

There is **no ESLint and no Prettier**. `eslint-disable` comments are dead code — do
not add them. Rule exceptions belong in `.oxlintrc.json`, with a comment saying why.

`noUncheckedIndexedAccess` is on: `array[i]` is `T | undefined`. Handle it; do not
cast it away.
